/* JAVASCRIPT LEARNING PLAN FOR PETER.*/

//WEEK 1

// Variables and Data Types: // Declaring variables with var, let, and const.: // Data types: numbers, strings, booleans, objects, arrays.: https://youtu.be/9WIJQDvt4Us


//WEEK 2 // Operators: // Arithmetic operators (+, -, *, /, %). // Comparison operators (==, ===, !=, !==, >, <, >=, <=). // Logical operators (&&, ||, !).

//WEEK 3 // Control Flow: // If statements. // Switch statements. // Loops: for, while, do-while,forEach

// WEEK 4 // Functions: // Declaring functions. // Parameters and return values. // Anonymous functions and arrow functions.

//WEEK 5 // Arrays: // Creating arrays. // Accessing and modifying array elements. // Array methods: push, pop, shift, unshift, slice, splice, indexof, includes,toUppercase,toLowercase

// WEEK 6 // Objects: // Creating objects. // Accessing and modifying object properties. // Object methods.

//WEEK 7 // Events: // Handling events (click, submit, keypress, etc.). // Event listeners. // DOM Manipulation: // Selecting elements. // Modifying HTML content, attributes, and styles. // Creating and removing elements. // Error Handling: // Using try, catch, and finally. // Understanding common JavaScript errors.

//WEEK 8: // Asynchronous JavaScript: // Callback functions. // Promises. // Async/await. 
// AJAX and Fetch API: // Making asynchronous requests to servers. // Handling responses.

// Local Storage and Session Storage: // Storing data locally in the browser.

// JSON (JavaScript Object Notation): // Understanding JSON format. // Parsing and stringifying JSON data.

// WEEK 9: // ES6+ Features: // Template literals. // Destructuring assignments.



